<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Questions on relationship between races and factions</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?Maxx">Maxx</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 11:31 p.m. 17/3/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Questions on relationship between races and factions<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR></STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>I was in P2/P3, and have just gotten EQ today. I'm quite out of the loop on the state of the game. Could someone in the know explain how the relationship between races and factions is working? I'm particular interested in how certain evil classes in normally neutral or even good races survive, or can get into the favor of the pure evil races like dark elves. For example, how does a gnome or erudite necromancer realisitic survive? Can this race/class become a friend to dark elves and be bound eventually to Neriak in the same way such races can be bound to rivendale? Can a human shadow knight who worships Cazic Thule become welcome in Grobb because he serves the same god? Does anyone have a clue generally or in particular on how these types of things work?

<BR>
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
